## Severity
Minor
## Dimension
dry
## Location
src/tools/web.rs:37-58 (execute_web_fetch) and src/tools/web.rs:179-200 (execute_web_browser)
## Violation
Both tool entry points format a `FetchResult` into the agent-facing string using identical logic — title heading, URL header, content append, 50000-char truncate with a "content truncated" suffix. The 50000 magic constant is also duplicated.

```rust
// execute_web_fetch
if let Some(title) = fetch_result.title { let _ = write!(output, "# {title}\n\n"); }
let _ = write!(output, "URL: {}\n\n", fetch_result.url);
output.push_str(&fetch_result.content);
if output.len() > 50000 {
    output = format!("{}...\n\n(content truncated, {} total chars)", safe_truncate(&output, 50000), output.len());
}
```

The runtime-dispatch boilerplate (`Handle::try_current` -> `block_in_place` else `Runtime::new`) is also duplicated between `execute_web_fetch` and `execute_web_search`.
## Mandated refactor
Extract a `format_fetch_result(result: FetchResult, max_len: usize) -> String` helper and call it from both tool functions, with `const MAX_OUTPUT_CHARS: usize = 50_000`. Extract `block_on_in_any_context<F>(fut: F) -> F::Output` for the runtime-dispatch boilerplate.
